                    <idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/person/1299</idno>
                    <idno type="FIEY">227</idno>
                    <sex value="M" source="#bib1299-2">male</sex>
                    <death when="0421" syriaca-computed-start="0421-01-01" source="#bib1299-2">0421</death>
                    <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bib1299-2">Sa legende a ete resumee par Nau, d'apres un manuscrit du xne siecle, dans son
"Resume" (1917), 3- 12.
BS, VI, 353 (J .-M. Sauget).</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-1299">Jacob the Recluse fled for the desert
            of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/715">Egypt</placeName> during the persecution
          of the emperor Julian. He then headed to East to <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/1452">Mesopotamia</placeName> with companions. They lived
          in a tower. Eventually he built a monastery at <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2">Salah</placeName> in <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/221">Ṭur
          ʿAbdin</placeName>.</note>
                    <event type="attestation" xml:id="attestation1299-1" source="#bib1299-2">
                        <p xml:lang="en">Yaʿqōb is commemorated in <title ref="http://syriaca.org/work/1368">Jacob the Recluse (text)</title>.</p>
                    </event>
                    <event type="attestation" xml:id="attestation1299-2" source="#bib1299-2">
